SUMMARY:Memory Café - A Dementia-Friendly Social Gathering
DESCRIPTION:For adults with dementia and their caregivers\, this event offers a welcoming\, safe\, calming space for socializing\, music\, art and reminiscing every month. \nA “Memory Café” is a dementia-friendly social gathering for individuals with early-stage memory loss or mild cognitive decline and their care givers. \nThe meetings will be held in a safe and comfortable environment where people can interact and socialize with others having similar experiences. At the gatherings participants can get support in a non-judgmental setting\, while enjoying the benefits of music for the brain. \nThe meetings will be run by Lisy Espindola\, LCSW and Kim McLennon\, MSW and music therapist. Lunch and/or snacks will be served. \nThis is a joint program between Lifelong Montclair at the Township of Montclair and the Montclair Public Library. \nAttendance is free but registration is required. Questions? Call 973-744-3278. \nShare this:\n				Share on Facebook (Opens in new window)\n				Facebook\n			\n				Share on Bluesky (Opens in new window)\n				Bluesky\n			\n				Share on LinkedIn (Opens in new window)\n				LinkedIn\n			\n				Share on Threads (Opens in new window)\n				Threads\n			\n				Share on Nextdoor (Opens in new window)\n				Nextdoor\n			\n				Share on WhatsApp (Opens in new window)\n				WhatsApp\n			\n				Email a link to a friend (Opens in new window)\n				Email
URL:https://montclairlocal.news/event/memory-cafe-a-dementia-friendly-social-gathering-3/
LOCATION:Montclair Public Library\, 50 South Fullerton Avenue\, Montclair\, New Jersey\, 07042\, United States
